*   WP:5P2[WP:5P2](/Wikipedia:5P2)

## Wikipedia is free content that anyone can use, edit, and distribute

This one often comes as a surprise to those who mistakenly believe their contributions are sacrosanct. All editors, whether they realize it or not, [freely license their work to the public](/Wikipedia:C) under terms that permit broad reuse. This means, quite unequivocally, that no editor [owns an article](/Wikipedia:OWN). The concept of ownership is a human construct ill-suited for a collaborative, evolving repository of knowledge. Any contributions, regardless of the effort or ego invested, can and may be [mercilessly edited](/Wikipedia:E) and [redistributed](/Wikipedia:REUSE) by anyone, for almost any purpose, provided the licensing terms are met. It's a rather efficient, if brutal, system for collective knowledge refinement.

Naturally, this freedom doesn't extend to outright theft. Respect for [copyright](/Wikipedia:CV) laws is paramount, and one must never [plagiarize](/Wikipedia:PLAG) from any sources. While borrowing [non-free media](/Wikipedia:F) (such as copyrighted images or audio) is sometimes permitted under the doctrine of [fair use](/Fair_use), editors are strongly encouraged to exhaust all avenues for finding free alternatives first. The ideal is a completely open resource, unburdened by the proprietary claims that so often stifle the spread of information. It's a pragmatic concession to legal realities, not an endorsement of restriction.

